NFL Ratings Mysteries, Rhode vs. Skims, A Brady Room Shake-Up
-------------------------------------------------------------

Welcome back to The Daily Courant, your afternoon digest of Puck=E2=80=99s =
best new reporting.

First up today, Leigh Ann Caldwell chronicles the abject chaos that envelop=
ed Washington in the 48-hour window before Trump=E2=80=99s Office of Manage=
ment and Budget rescinded its $3 trillion federal spending freeze=E2=80=94a=
 saga that illustrates the new administration=E2=80=99s determination to te=
st the limits of presidential power, and that foreshadows a looming congres=
sional clash.

Plus, below the fold:
Bill Cohan takes the long view on the DeepSeek-inspired Nasdaq crash. Dylan=
 Byers scrutinizes the new Brady Room seating chart and another big exit at=
 Politico. Rachel Strugatz scoops Hailey Bieber=E2=80=99s new retail strate=
gy. And in an Inner Circle-exclusive dispatch, Julie Davich and Arta founde=
r Adam Fields discuss his zealous quest to digitize the =E2=80=9Clast front=
ier=E2=80=9D of art sales.

Meanwhile,
on the pods: Tara Palmeri is joined by Oxford Strategies consultant Shanti =
Stanton on Somebody=E2=80=99s Gotta Win to consider the legal limits of Tru=
mp=E2=80=99s executive orders=E2=80=94and Elon=E2=80=99s role in the chaos.=
 And on The Powers That Be, Peter Hamby connects with John Ourand to dissec=
t the NFL=E2=80=99s season-long ratings decline.

